label: Polio serotype 1 seroconversion failure
definition: Seroconversion failure was derived based on the child's serum neutralizing antibodies (SNA) at 40 weeks (SNAwk40) and the maternal-antibody adjusted SNA at 18 weeks (SNAwk18). The participant was considered to have failed to seroconvert if a) SNAwk18 ¬≤ 2.833 and SNAwk40 ¬≤ 3 or b)  2.833< SNAwk18 ¬≤ 8.5 and (SNAwk40 - SNAwk18) < 2 or c) 8.5 < SNAwk18 <10.5 and SNAwk40 < 10.5. Participants with SNAwk18  ¬≥ 10.5 were excluded.
codebookDescription:
Sabin 1 seroconversion failure * 1.For subjects 2.833< SNAwk18_adjust ¬≤ 8.5
Seroconversion failure if (SNAwk40 - SNAwk18_adjust)<2
2.For subjects 8.5 < SNAwk18_adjust <10.5 
   Seroconversion failure if SNAwk40 < 10.5
3. For subjects SNAwk18_adjust ¬≤ 2.833
   Seroconversion failure if SNAwk40 ¬≤ 3
4. For subjects SNAwk18_adjust¬≥10.5, excluded.

label: Bacille Calmette-Guerin (BCG) vaccine
definition: Participants were supposed to receive BCG at 6 weeks if they didn't receive it at birth.
codebookDescription: 6c. BCG (only if not given at birth)

label: Inactivated poliovirus (IPV) vaccine
definition: Depending on randomization, participants were set to receive OPV or IPV at 39 weeks.
codebookDescription: 5b. Inactivated Polio Vaccine (IPV) Treatment group B and D only)

label: Measles vaccine
definition: Participants were supposed to receive the measles vaccine at 40 weeks.

label: Oral poliovirus (OPV) vaccine
definition: Participants were supposed to receive OPV at 6, 10, 14, and 52 weeks. Depending on randomization, they were set to receive OPV or IPV at 39 weeks.
codebookDescription: 6b.  Oral Polio Vaccine (OPV) | 5b.  Oral Polio Vaccine (OPV) | 5a. Oral Polio Vaccine (OPV) Treatment group A and C only)

label: Pentavalent vaccine
definition: Participants were supposed to receive the pentavalent vaccine (diphtheria, tetanus, pertussis, hepatitis B, and Haemophilus influenza type b) at 6, 10, and 14 weeks.

label: Rotarix vaccine
definition: Participants were randomized as to whether they would receive Rotarix or not, which was given at 10 and 17 weeks.
codebookDescription: 5c. Rotarix (Groups A and B only | 5a. Rotarix (Treatment group A and B only)

label: Rubella vaccine
definition: Participants were supposed to receive the rubella vaccine at 40 weeks.

label: Polio vaccination dose per protocol
definition: Whether the participant received all intervention doses even if outside the visit window. The justification for relaxing the vaccination window requirement is partially based on the WHO recommendations which emphasize getting the required doses rather than exact ages for receiving the doses and the pragmatic concern of how far outside the window do we set the threshold.√ä
codebookDescription: Received all intervention doses even if outside the visit window

label: Polio vaccination per protocol
definition: Whether strictly per protocol as described here. The participant (1) must have received all doses of vaccine as in protocol and according to assigned treatment arm, (2) received√äno extra vaccinations outside the protocol, (3) received all vaccinations as per vaccination window defined in the protocol, (4) should not have been terminated before the vaccination dose.
codebookDescription: whether strictly per protocol as described below under PP set

label: Age last exclusively breastfed (days)

definition: Number of days of breastfeeding with or without other food sources.
codebookDescription: Number of days of any breast feeding (Includes exclusive BF as well)

codebookValues: 1 = Breast Milk(BM); 2=Top Milk (TM); 3 = BM+ TM; 4 = Water/ Sugar or Water/ Honey

label: Arm recoil
codebookValues:
1 = Remains extended 180 degrees, or random movements (0 points); 2 = Minimal flexion, 140-180 degrees (1 point); 3 = Small amount of flexion, 110-140 degrees (2 points); 4 = Moderate flexion, 90-100 degrees (3 points); 5 = Brisk return to full flexion, <90 degrees (4 points);
9 = Missing

label: Breast
codebookValues:
1 = Imperceptible (-1 point); 2 = Barely perceptible (0 points); 3 = Flat areola, no bud (1 point); 4 = Stippled areola, 1-2 mm bud (2 points); 5 = Raised areola, 3-4 mm bud (3 points); 6 = Full areola, 5-10 mm bud (4 points);
9 = Missing

label: Estimated gestational age (weeks)
definition: Based on the calculated gestational age score.

label: Eye and ear
codebookValues: 1 = Lids fused, tightly (-2 points); 2 = Lids fused, loosely (-1 point); 3 = Lids open, pinna flat, stays folded (0 points); 4 = Slightly curved pinna, soft with slow recoil (1 point); 5 = Well-curved pinna, soft but ready recoil (2 points); 6 = Formed and firm, with instant recoil (3 points); 7 = Thick cartilage, ear stiff (4 points); NA=Not Available/Not applicable

label: Female genitals
codebookValues: 1 = Clitoris prominent, labia flat (-1 point); 2 = Prominent clitoris, small labia minora (0 points); 3 = Prominent clitoris, enlarging minora (1 point); 4 = Majora and minora equally prominent (2 points); 5 = Majora large, minora small (3 points); 6 = Majora cover clitoris and minora (4 points); 7 = NA, the child is male (0 points); NA=Not Available/Not applicable

label: Gestational age score
definition: Total score based on all gestational age categories.

label: Heel to ear
codebookValues:
1= (-1 Point); 2=(0 points); 3=(1 points); 4=(2 points); 5=(3 points);  6=(4 points);;
9 = Missing

label: Lanugo
codebookValues: 1 = None (-1 point); 2 = Sparse (0 points); 3 = Abundant (1 point); 4 = Thinning (2 points); 5 = Bald areas (3 points); 6 = Mostly bald (4 points); NA=Not Available/Not applicable

label: Male genitals
codebookValues: 1 = Scrotum flat, smooth (-1 point); 2 = Scrotum empty, faint rugae (0 points); 3 = Testes in upper cannal, rare rugae (1 point); 4 = Testes descending, few rugae (2 points); 5 = Testes down, good rugae (3 points); 6 = Testes pendulous, deep rugae (4 points); 7 = NA, the child is female (0 points), 99 = missing

label: Plantar creases
codebookValues:
1 = Heel-toe <40 mm (-2 points); 2 = Heel-toe 40-50 mm (-1 point); 3 = Heel-toe >50 mm, no creases (0 points); 4 = Faint red marks (1 point); 5 = Anterior transverse crease only (2 points); 6 = Creases over anterior 2/3 (3 points); 7 = Creases over entire sole (4 points);
9 = Missing

label: Popliteal angle
codebookValues:
1 = 180 degrees (-1 point); 2 = 160 degrees (0 points); 3 = 140 degrees (1 point); 4 = 120 degrees (2 points); 5 = 100 degrees (3 points); 6 = 90 degrees (4 points); 7 = <90 degrees (5 points);
9 = Missing

label: Posture
codebookValues:
1 = Arms and legs extended (0 points ); 2 = Slight or moderate flexion of hips and knees (1 point); 3 = Moderate to strong flexion of hips and knees (2 points); 4 = Legs flexed and abducted, arms slightly flexed (3 points); 5 = Full flexion of arms and legs (4 points);
9 = Missing

label: Scarf sign
codebookValues: 1 = Elbow reaches or nears level of opposite shoulder (-1 point); 2 = Elbow crosses opposite anterior axillary line (0 points); 3 = Elbow reaches opposite anterior axillary line (1 point); 4 = Elbow at midline (2 points); 5 = Elbow does not reach midline (3 points); 6 = Elbow does not cross proximate axillary line (4 points); NA=Not Available/Not applicable

label: Skin
codebookValues:
1 = Sticky, friable, transparent (-1 point); 2 = Gelatinous red, translucent (0 points); 3 = Smooth pink, visible veins (1 point); 4 = Superficial peeling and/or rash, few veins (2 points); 5 = Cracking, pale areas, rare veins (3 points); 6 = Parchment, deep cracking, no vessels (4 points); 7 = Leathery, cracked, wrinkled (5 points);
9 = Missing

label: Square window
codebookValues: 1 = >90 degrees (-1 point); 2 = 90 degrees (0 points); 3 = 60 degrees (1 point); 4 = 45 degrees (2 points); 5 = 30 degrees (3 points); 6 = 0 degrees (4 points); NA=Not Available/Not applicable

label: Leptin receptor genotype
definition: Uses the marker C___8722581_10 which tests for Q223R in the leptin receptor. A codes to glutamine (Q), while G codes to arginine (R)

label: Lewis secretor
definition: Whether the participant has the secretor (Se) allele.
codebookValues: Positive=1, Negative=2 and inconclusive=3  / 1= result_a+ve, result_b+ve OR 1= result_a-ve, result_b+ve; 2= result_a+ve, result_b-ve; 3 (Inconclusive)= result_a-ve, result_b-ve

label: Lewis type
definition: The Lewis type category of the participant. a+ b- implies the participant has the Le allele but not the Se allele. a- b+ implies the participant has the Le allele and the Se allele. a- b- implies the participant has the Le recessive allele and may or may not have the Se allele. a+ b+ can be seen transiently in infants since secretor function increase with age or can suggest the participant has a weak Se allele.

label: PRKCA genotype
definition: The genotype for the top cryptosporidium-associated SNP in PRKCA (rs58296998_T). This is in an additive format for the minor (risk) allele.

label: Diphtheria toxoid IgG titer (IU/mL), by MIA result
definition: A multiplexed immuno assay was used. 0.01 IU/mL is protective. All values <0.001 IU/mL or below the standard curve were set to 0.001 IU/mL. Assessed at 53 weeks.
codebookValues: 0.01 IU/ml are considered protective / values below 0.001 IU/ml or below the standard curve for Dtxd or Ttx are set to 0.001 IU/ml, - 9 = missing

label: Filamentous hemagglutinin IgG titer (EU/mL), by MIA result
definition: A multiplexed immuno assay was used. Filamentous hemagglutinin (FHA) is included in pertussis vaccines. Values below 1 EU/mL or below the standard curve were set to 1 EU/mL. Assessed at 53 weeks.

label: Haemophilus influenzae type B IgG titer (ng/mL), by MIA result
definition: A multiplexed immuno assay was used. Values >1.0 ng/mL are considered protective. All values <0.01 ng/mL or below the standard curve were set to 0.01 ng/mL. Assessed at 53 weeks.
codebookValues: >1.0 ng/ml is considered protective;   -9= not done / all values below 0.01 ng/ml or below the standard curve for Hib are set to 0.01 ng/ml, - 9 = missing

label: Measles IgG titer (IU/mL), by MIA result
definition: A multiplexed immuno assay was used. 0.12 IU/mL is protective. All values <0.001 IU/mL or below the standard curve were set to 0.001 IU/mL. Assessed at 53 weeks.
codebookValues: 0.12 IU/ml is protective;   -9= not done / all values below 0.001 IU/ml or below the standard curve for Measles are set to 0.001 IU/ml

label: Pertactin IgG titer (EU/mL), by MIA result
definition: A multiplexed immuno assay was used. Pertactin (PRN) is included in pertussis vaccines. Values below 1 EU/mL or below the standard curve were set to 1 EU/mL. Assessed at 53 weeks.

label: Pertussis toxin IgG titer (EU/mL), by MIA result
definition: A multiplexed immuno assay was used. Values >62.5 EU/mL are indicative for infection in the past year. Values >125 EU/mL are indicitive for recent infection. Values below 1 EU/mL or below the standard curve were set to 1 EU/mL. Assessed at 53 weeks.
codebookDescription: Vaccine response to B. Pertussis toxin (EU/ml)
codebookValues: levels >62.5 LU/ml indicative for infection in the past year ; levels over 125 LU/ml for recent infection;   -9= not done / values below 1 EU/ml or below the standard curve are set to 1 EU/ml for all pertussis antigens
